---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import QuickAnswer from '../components/QuickAnswer.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import PersonSchema from '../components/schema/PersonSchema.astro';
import AboutPageSchema from '../components/schema/AboutPageSchema.astro';
import BreadcrumbSchema from '../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const quickAnswer =
  'Percolate is an iOS app for specialty coffee drinkers, built and run by ' +
  'one independent developer. It catalogs your shelf, logs every cup, ' +
  'and recommends bags you already own. It is not a roaster, not a ' +
  'scraper of competitor sites, and not an ad platform. Percolate is free; ' +
  'it makes money only from disclosed roaster affiliate links.';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Percolate — who runs it, what it is, what it isn't, and how it makes money."
  path="/about"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <AboutPageSchema />
    <PersonSchema />
    <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[{ name: 'About', url: `${SITE.url}/about` }]} />
  </Fragment>

  <p class="brand">{SITE.name}</p>
  <h1>About Percolate</h1>
  <p class="effective">A drinker's coffee shelf and cupping log — built and run by one person.</p>

  <QuickAnswer text={quickAnswer} />

  <h2>Who runs Percolate?</h2>
  <p>
    Percolate is built and operated by <strong>{SITE.founder.name}</strong>,
    an independent developer and longtime specialty-coffee drinker, and published by
    {SITE.legalEntity}, the developer's own company. There is no outside
    investor and no advertising network behind the app.
    Decisions about features, privacy, and direction are made by one person,
    and that person answers the email at
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What is Percolate?</h2>
  <p>
    Percolate is an iOS app for specialty coffee drinkers. It does four things
    well: catalog your shelf with status, origin, process, and roast; log every
    cup with a structured cupping note for aroma, acidity, body, and flavor;
    build a taste profile from your real shelf and the cups you brew; and
    suggest what to brew today from bags you already own. A yearly
    Year in Coffee recap closes the loop with the stats only your own data
    can produce.
  </p>

  <h2>What Percolate is not</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>It is <strong>not a roaster</strong>. The app does not sell or roast coffee. When you want to buy, we link out to roasters and specialty retailers and may earn a small commission.</li>
    <li>It is <strong>not a scraper</strong> of other coffee sites. Our catalog comes from roaster product data and manual curation.</li>
    <li>It is <strong>not a marketplace</strong>. There are no buy/sell flows, no auctions, no green-bean exchange.</li>
    <li>It does <strong>not show ads</strong>. There are no ads anywhere in the app or on this site.</li>
    <li>It does <strong>not sell or share your data</strong> for cross-user ad targeting. Your shelf and cupping log are private by default. See the <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for the full breakdown.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How Percolate makes money</h2>
  <p>
    Percolate is <strong>free</strong> to download and use &mdash; there is no
    subscription, no paywall, and no Pro tier. Every feature is included:
    building your shelf, logging cupping notes, scanning labels, the flavor
    quiz, and the Year in Coffee recap. There are no ads and we never sell
    your data.
  </p>
  <p>
    The only revenue stream is transparent. Coffee detail pages may include
    <strong>&ldquo;Buy from&rdquo;</strong> links to the roaster or to
    specialty retailers. When you use one of those links and purchase, we may
    earn a small commission at no cost to you. This is disclosed on the page
    where the link appears and in the <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
    The price you pay is the same.
  </p>

  <h2>Why an independent developer built this</h2>
  <p>
    The coffee internet has not been served well. The most-cited reference
    sites are dated, ad-heavy, and treat the drinker like a row in a database.
    Newer entrants are feature-thin and focused on discovery for shoppers, not
    on drinkers who already keep a half-dozen bags on the shelf and want to
    actually dial them in. Percolate is built for the drinker who needs a shelf,
    a cupping log, and a private taste profile in one place &mdash; without ads,
    without scraping, and without being pushed toward the next purchase.
  </p>

  <h2>Editorial standards</h2>
  <p>
    Articles published on this site are written by {SITE.founder.name} based
    on first-hand experience as a coffee drinker and on cited primary sources
    (roaster notes, the SCA cupping protocol, processing and roasting references,
    and other public sources). When a fact comes from somewhere other than direct
    experience, it is linked. When something is an opinion, it is labeled.
  </p>
  <p>
    Articles are dated, and the date is updated only when the content
    actually changes &mdash; not just to make the page look fresh.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Press, partnership, or product feedback:
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>.
    There is no DM channel &mdash; email is the canonical contact.
  </p>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
